<br>
Your Isp also seems high for a nuclear light bulb. Las Alamos did a number of studies on GCNR in the late 1980's and early 1990's and they thought Isp's of between 1600-2000s were possible for a nuclear light bulb, although it might be possible to reach 3000s with major advance.<br>
